==German==

===Phrase===
'''[[Sieg]] [[heil#German|Heil]]'''

# {{archaic|lang=de}} '''Sieg Heil''' (literally roughly: Hail, victory!)

====Usage notes====
'''''Sieg Heil''''' became the salute of the German National Socialist (Nazi) party in 1920's. It developed to the so called {{w|Hitler salute}}, the use of which was later made obligatory to all Germans in the [[Third Reich]]. After the [[WWII]] the public use of any form of the Hitler salute was criminalized in Germany and Austria. In Germany it is punishable with up to three years in prison.

